  "blocker": "PR #486 fixed the canary ordering so the cache-arm request now reports 175 cached tokens for the 175-token generated handoff prefix, and Cachet hydrated all expected SGLang pages through the live custom_params request path. The run is still not a publishable SGLang benchmark because baseline and cache live quality returned identical repeated filler output, and the model-quality canary failed when run after cache/baseline checks. A previous canary-first diagnostic passed the canary before perturbing cache validation, so the remaining blocker appears to be SGLang/Qwen generation quality or prefix-cache state/order after live checks, not Cachet handoff hydration."
